DescriptionAdapternextcloud.message: The legacy option is compatible with at least version v0.11 of the Bookmarks app. It will emulate folders using tags containing the folder path. It is not recommended to use this for new accounts.

DescriptionAdapternextcloudfolders.message: The option 'Nextcloud Bookmarks' is compatible with at least version v0.14 of the Bookmarks app.

DescriptionAdapterwebdav.message: The WebDAV option syncs your bookmarks by storing them in an XBEL file in the provided WebDAV share. There is no accompanying web UI for this option and you can use it with any WebDAV-compatible server.

DescriptionBookmarksfile.message: a path to the bookmarks file relative to your WebDAV URL (all folders in the path must already exist). e.g. personal_stuff/bookmarks.xbel

DescriptionChoosefolder.message: Set an existing folder to sync

DescriptionFunddevelopment.message: I'm using this opportunity to ask you for a donation in order to support the maintenance of this project and make this endeavor more sustainable. You can find the supported payment providers below. Any amount is appreciated. Thank you!ðŸ’™

DescriptionGithubsponsors.message: Make a regular donation via GitHub sponsors to support the project

DescriptionLiberapay.message: Make a regular donation via Liberapay to support the project

DescriptionLocalfolder.message: This is the local bookmarks folder in this browser that will be synced to the server. By default a new empty folder will be created for you in this browser, if you want to sync an existing folder, select it here. (Note: You can now sync the root folder across different browser vendors out of the box.)

DescriptionNestedSync.message: You can nest accounts so that a parent folder belongs to one account and a child folder to a different account. Do you want to include this account's local folder in any potential parent folder sync from a different account?

DescriptionNoAccount.message: Create a new account to sync your bookmarks.

DescriptionOpencollective.message: Make a regular donation via OpenCollective to support the project

DescriptionParallelsync.message: Tick this box to process multiple folders in parallel in order to speed the synchronization. This feature is experimental and makes it harder to read the debug logs.

DescriptionPaypal.message: Make a one-time donation via paypal to support the project

DescriptionRemoveaccount.message: Delete this account (this will not remove your bookmarks)

DescriptionReset.message: Reset synchronized folder to create a new one

DescriptionResetcache.message: Tick this box to reset the cache so that the next synchronization run is guaranteed not to delete any data and merely merges server and local bookmarks together

DescriptionServerfolder.message: This is the path prefix under which this account will operate on the server. E.g. if you use ''/work', all your bookmarks will be created on the server with this path prefixed to their original path (the one relative to the local folder you specified above). This allows you to separate your server bookmarks into multiple 'profiles'. Leave this empty to use no prefix at all.

DescriptionSetkey.message: When you set a pass phrase you will have to enter this pass phrase everytime you start your browser if you want to access and synchronize your bookmarks.

DescriptionStrategy.message: This option determines how to synchronize the bookmarks tree on the server with the one in this browser. Usually you will want to keep changes to both trees if they are compatible, but sometimes you might want to force the local version onto the server, or vice versa.

DescriptionSyncinterval.message: The timespan between two sync runs in minutes. Default is 15 minutes.

DescriptionUpdated.message: Congrats, the latest update of floccus has arrived on your machine!
